hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Relevant equations:
   $$\dot\omega_{GR}=\frac{3(GM)^{3/2}}{c^2a^{5/2}(1-e^2)},\quad
     J_2=\frac12\,k_2\frac{m}{M}\Bigl(\frac{R}{a}\Bigr)^3,\quad
     \dot\omega_{Tide}=-\frac{3J_2R^2\sqrt{GM}}{2a^{7/2}(1-e^2)}.$$
2. Substitute $J_2$ into $\dot\omega_{Tide}$:
   $$\dot\omega_{Tide}
     =-\frac{3}{2}\frac{\bigl(\frac12k_2\frac{m}{M}(\frac{R}{a})^3\bigr)R^2\sqrt{GM}}
              {a^{7/2}(1-e^2)}
     =-\frac{3k_2\,m\,R^5\sqrt{GM}}{4\,M\,a^{13/2}(1-e^2)}.$$
3. Set total precession to zero:
   $$\dot\omega_{GR}+\dot\omega_{Tide}=0
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     \frac{3(GM)^{3/2}}{c^2a^{5/2}(1-e^2)}
     =\frac{3k_2\,m\,R^5\sqrt{GM}}{4\,M\,a^{13/2}(1-e^2)}.$$
4. Simplify, cancelling common factors ($3$, $\sqrt{GM}$, $1-e^2$):
   $$\frac{GM}{c^2a^{5/2}}
     =\frac{k_2\,m\,R^5}{4\,M\,a^{13/2}}
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     4\,G\,M^2\,a^4=c^2\,k_2\,m\,R^5.$$
5. Solve for $a$:
   $$a^4=\frac{c^2\,k_2\,m\,R^5}{4\,G\,M^2}
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     a=\Bigl(\frac{c^2\,k_2\,m\,R^5}{4\,G\,M^2}\Bigr)^{\frac{1}{4}}.$$
